# QuizGen – AI-Powered Quiz & Mock Test Generator

QuizGen is a modern, lightweight backend application that automates the creation of practice tests. By leveraging Generative AI, the system converts unstructured study notes or topic prompts into structured, interactive multiple-choice quizzes, evaluates user submissions, and tracks learning progress over time.

This project is built using a decoupled **Model-View-Controller (MVC)** architecture without front-end dependencies, returning clean, human-readable plain-text test papers and scorecard reports directly in the browser or HTTP clients.

---

## 🚀 Key Features

*   **AI Quiz Generation:** Automatically creates custom-length quizzes (e.g., 3, 5, 10 questions) based on raw notes using the **Google Gemini 1.5 Flash API**.
*   **Plain-Text Visual Rendering:** Returns formatted test papers and scorecards instead of raw JSON, optimizing readability for backend testing.
*   **Intuitive Attempt Evaluation:** Allows users to submit answers as simple letters (`A, B, C, D`) which are automatically graded against database records.
*   **Progress Tracking & Analytics:** Logs student attempt history in MySQL and provides aggregated performance reports (total attempts, average score percentage, and highest score).
*   **Auto-Generated Documentation:** Interactive REST API testing dashboard powered by **Swagger UI (OpenAPI)**.

---

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

*   **Language:** Java 21 (LTS)
*   **Framework:** Spring Boot 3.3.0 (Spring Web, Spring Data JPA)
*   **Database:** MySQL
*   **AI Service:** Google Gemini AI API
*   **JSON Processor:** Jackson (ObjectMapper)
*   **API Documentation:** Swagger UI (Springdoc-openapi)
*   **Build Tool:** Maven

---

## 📊 Database Schema

The database consists of three relational tables managed via Hibernate:
*   `quizzes`: Stores quiz metadata (ID, title, topic, and creation timestamp).
*   `questions`: Stores MCQ question text, options A/B/C/D, correct index, and maps back to its parent quiz using a **One-to-Many** relationship.
*   `quiz_attempts`: Tracks attempt scores, total questions, and timestamps linked to the attempted quiz.

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites
*   Java Development Kit (JDK) 21 or higher
*   MySQL Server running locally
*   Google Gemini API Key (obtained from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/))

### 1. Database Creation
Open your MySQL client and run the following command to create a blank database:
```sql
CREATE DATABASE quizgen;


2. Configuration
Navigate to src/main/resources/application.properties and configure your database credentials and API key:

properties


spring.datasource.username=YOUR_MYSQL_USERNAME
spring.datasource.password=YOUR_MYSQL_PASSWORD
gemini.api.key=YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY



3. Run the Application
Open the project in your IDE (VS Code / IntelliJ IDEA) and run the QuizgenApplication.java file. The server will start on port 8081 (or 8080).

📋 API Testing Guide
Open your browser and navigate to the Swagger dashboard: 👉 http://localhost:8081/swagger-ui/index.html

Endpoint Workflow:
Generate Quiz: Call POST /api/quizzes/generate by entering a topic, notes (e.g. OOP inheritance basics), and target count of questions.
View Quiz: Copy the returned Quiz ID and retrieve the quiz format using GET /api/quizzes/{id}.
Submit Answers: Grade your answers using POST /api/quizzes/{id}/attempt by passing a list of letters (e.g., A, C, B).
View Performance Stats: Get your history log via GET /api/quizzes/attempts or your metrics report via GET /api/quizzes/analytics.


4. Save the file (`Ctrl + S`).
